commitResults.messageTitle: Add echo feature, refactor greet and exit
Add store and list messages feature and refactor
commitResults.messageBody:
Chatbot commands are now exclusively lower case.

This is to keep behaviour consistent in supporting future commands.

Looping behaviour is no longer separated to a function.

This is to allow for easier branching of behaviour as more commands are
supported. Future iterations can look into creating a separate chatbot
class and instance separate from the main() function.

Duke:
- Remove all previous functions and replace with an echo() function.
- Standard messages are now stored as constants.

TaskList:
- markTask() and unmarkTask() now return String as output feedback.

Duke is refactored as many functions serve to only print a message.
It is redundant to create many functions to print to output.
echo() serves as a way to print output through the chatbot.

TaskList functions should return a message that will be sent as
feedback for the users. This is to make the chatbot feel more
responsive and users are aware of actions executed by chatbot.

ToDo: Task with no datetime attached.

Deadline: Task with a specified due date.

Event: Task with a specified start datetime and end datetime.

- User input to add tasks are now changed.
- TaskList addTask() function is slightly modified to immediately take
  in a created task.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add error handling and refactor task creation
commitResults.messageBody:
TaskException: Exceptions for when configuring tasks.

UnknownCommandException: Exception when user input unknown command.

Tasks are now created through factory methods from their respective
tasks. Tasks are also now created based on input directly after given
command.

This is to allow TaskExceptions to be thrown exclusively by Tasks
instead of the main program.
Prefer to run files from project root folder.

Also add such that adding and deleting tasks now outputs total number of
tasks left in the list.

Errors for delete task are also accounted for.

Duke program is handling all tasks.

It is good to have greater separation of concerns to reduce coupling.

Ui class helps separate printing of outputs.
Class is not yet used in program.

Code is tightly coupled with no clear separations of handling.

Command class are now introduced together with Parser and Storage
to better separate concerns. Additionally, TaskException is now renamed
as CommandException to better represent the exception.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix bug for unmark, mark and delete
commitResults.messageBody: Input was not trimmed before parsing, causing commands to fail.

Important general changes:
1. Ui class is removed in favour of GUI with JavaFX.
2. Entry point of program has changed to Launcher.java instead of Duke.java

Command:
- Commands now return the String for response after calling command.

TaskList:
- loadTasks() now returns number of tasks that failed to load from
  improper formatting.

Minor changes:
- Renamed chatbot from Ted to Duke Zeh.

Add more line breaks where necessary such that formatting on GUI is
cleaner.

Program does not use any assertions, and have no validation of states
before running further operations.

This can cause the program to run with errors and cause unintended
consequences.

Assertions are added at various points of the script, mainly
Parser.java, Storage.java and Main.java.

This is done for early program termination in the case that important
assertions are not met.

Local variable tokens is reused to continually split the String
to get LocalDateTime information from splitting.

Can cause wrong information to be parsed if tokens as tokens are
overwritten at different points.

New local variables are created to extract LocalDateTime information.

This will prevent confusion and avoid splitting on wrong data.

In the future should avoid cases of reusing variables.

ByeCommand returns a magic String literal. The String is then recognized
by MainWindow.java to know when to exit the program.

Typo or change in message can cause program to work incorrectly as it as
a functional component apart from printing to output.

Storing the message as a constant under ByeCommand will allow for better
consistency and improve readability.

In the future should avoid magic literals, especially if it affects
logic in the code.

Same check on index is is done before retrieving or removing task from
markTask, unmarkTask and deleteTask.

Check condition uses some form of complex expression repeatedly.

Extract out the index bounds check into separate functions that get
and removes tasks from taskList. Also introduce new TaskListException
to handle such exceptions.
Add asserts
Merge branch-A-CodeQuality

Commands attempt to parse input to get parameters to create tasks within
constructor. Constructor is also reusing input parameter and reassigning
a trimmed input to overwrite input.

Same code is duplicated in parseData, with the exception of errors
thrown.

Parser class can include functions to parse input directly into
a task and still falls under responsibility of Parser.

This provides better encapsulation in turn providing better readability.

In the future, should better utilize Parser class to parse data from one
type to another.

Reduce complex logic in written code.

Changed StringBuilder to append String before returning as it looks
cleaner.
Merge branch-A-CodeQuality

Task have no separation in priorities.

Add different priority levels for user to better manage their tasks.
There are 3 priority levels, low, high and none. Default priority value
is none and there will be no indication beside listed task.
